# Project: Hex-Globe Kingdom Simulation

A tweakable Babylon.js sim of kingdoms spreading on a hex-tiled globe. Hobby
project: optimize for clarity, expandability, fast rule iteration — not prod.

## Before doing anything
Read `docs/PROJECT.md` (source of truth) and `docs/TASKS.md` (ordered checklist).
Work the tasks in order; don't skip ahead.

## Non-negotiables
- TypeScript strict. No `any`.
- Sim is **double-buffered**: read previous state, write next, swap. Never mutate
  the buffer you're reading from mid-tick.
- Discrete fixed ticks. Render loop is separate from sim ticks.
- **`core/` and `sim/` must NOT import Babylon.** Rendering is a read-only view.
- Terrain/features are **composition** on `Tile`, never subclasses of `Tile`.
- Every new tunable goes in `SimConfig` AND gets a UI slider.

## When unsure
PROJECT.md §3 lists Open Questions that are deliberately undecided. If a task
hits one, **stop and ask the human** — do not silently pick. State which rules
you applied in your reply.
